<h2>➕ 2. Python Libraries</h2>

<h3>Standard Libraries</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>random</strong>: generate random numbers, shuffle lists</li>
<li><strong>datetime</strong>: work with dates and times</li>
<li><strong>math</strong>: mathematical functions</li>
</ul>

<pre>import random
print(random.randint(1, 10))

from datetime import datetime
print(datetime.now())

import math
print(math.sqrt(16))</pre>

<h3>Optional Libraries</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>requests</strong>: access web APIs</li>
<li><strong>pandas</strong>: handle data in tables (DataFrames)</li>
</ul>

<pre>import pandas as pd

data = {"Name": ["Alice", "Bob"], "Age": [25, 30]}
df = pd.DataFrame(data)
print(df)</pre>

